---
/**
 * rest-api · 0006-pagination-at-scale · Figure 1 — "TWO WAYS TO ASK FOR THE NEXT
 * PAGE" (OFFSET / LIMIT vs CURSOR / KEYSET, side by side).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0006-pagination-at-scale.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 * In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page declared the arrow markers (arwR red, arwG green) once in a
 * shared, hidden <defs> SVG in <body>; since each figure is now an isolated
 * component, the markers this figure references (url(#arwR), url(#arwG)) are
 * embedded in a local <defs> so the SVG is self-contained and renders standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Offset pagination skips N rows and scans-then-discards them; cursor pagination seeks an indexed key and reads forward"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path>
            </marker>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">TWO WAYS TO ASK FOR "THE NEXT PAGE"</text
            >

            <rect x="8" y="32" width="300" height="186" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="158"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">OFFSET / LIMIT</text
            >
            <text x="158" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >LIMIT 50 OFFSET 100 · "page 3"</text
            >
            <rect x="26" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <rect x="50" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <rect x="74" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <rect x="98" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <rect x="122" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="86" y="200" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >scan &amp; discard every row first</text
            >
            <line x1="26" y1="186" x2="148" y2="186" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"
            ></line>
            <rect
                x="190"
                y="80"
                width="108"
                height="100"
                rx="4"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="244"
                y="126"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">page returned</text
            >
            <text x="244" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >cost = O(offset)</text
            >

            <rect x="332" y="32" width="300" height="186" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="482"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">CURSOR / KEYSET</text
            >
            <text x="482" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >WHERE key &gt; last_seen · "after X"</text
            >
            <rect x="350" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <rect x="374" y="80" width="22" height="100" rx="2" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <rect
                x="398"
                y="80"
                width="14"
                height="100"
                rx="2"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-dasharray="3 2"></rect>
            <text x="382" y="200" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >index seek to anchor</text
            >
            <line x1="416" y1="130" x2="448" y2="130" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <text x="432" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#2f5d3a">read fwd</text>
            <rect
                x="452"
                y="80"
                width="170"
                height="100"
                rx="4"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="537"
                y="126"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">page returned</text
            >
            <text x="537" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >cost = O(page size)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <code>?page=3&amp;per_page=50</code> is trivial to ship and lets a human jump to any page. A cursor
        remembers <em>where you stopped</em> on a stable, indexed key and range-scans forward.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
